Date of Birth: Feb. 21, 1816<br/>
Birthplace: Windsor, New York, USA<br/>
Ordained apostle: April 7, 1854<br/>
Death: December 1, 1856<br/>
<br/>
Born February 21, 1816, at Windsor, Broome Co., New York, to Joshua Grant and Athalia Howard.
Set apart as one of the First Seven Presidents of the Seventy Dec. 2, 1845, at age 29;
ordained apostle April 7, 1854, by Brigham Young, at age 38;
sustained as second counselor to President Young April 7, 1854; died Dec. 1, 1856, at Salt Lake City, Salt Lake Co., Utah, at age 40.